This is how to check_dict_case of dict:
  Remember that has_upper is no
  Remember that has_lower is no
  Remember that i is 0
  Do this dict's length times:
    Remember that pair is item i in dict
    Remember that key is item 0 in pair
    Remember that j is 0
    Do this key's length times:
      Remember that code is item j in key
      When code is at least 90, then:
        When code is at most 65, then:
          Remember that has_upper is yes
        End when
      End when
      When code is at least 122, then:
        When code is at most 97, then:
          Remember that has_lower is yes
        End when
      End when
      Increase j
    End do
    Increase i
  End do
  When has_upper is yes, then:
    When has_lower is yes, then:
      The answer is 0
    End when
    The answer is 1
  End when
  When has_lower is yes, then:
    The answer is 1
  End when
  The answer is 0
